The idea here is that:

 - For each row of the pyramid (so the row goes from 0 to `size` excluded)
 - We need to determine how many asterisks to print. If we are in the upper-half of the pyramid, it is the equal to the row we&#39;re at. It we are in the lower-half of the pyramid, it is equal to `size-1-row` (decreasing with the row increasing). So the count of asterisk is the minimum of `row` and `size-1-row`: this is factored in a single statement using `Math.min(size-1-row, row)`.

