I was also facing the same issue it mainly happens with fresh installations of eclipse or with adding a remote catalogue.

The archetype manager reads the catalogue if it gets invalid value we get that error.

# **how to solve** #

The file `\.metadata\.plugins\org.eclipse.m2e.core\archetypesInfo.xml` contains the archetype catalogues resetting it to the initial state solves it.

This is my template after i changed it.

    &lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;
    	&lt;archetypeCatalogs&gt;
    		&lt;catalog type=&quot;system&quot; id=&quot;internal&quot; enabled=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;
    		&lt;catalog type=&quot;system&quot; id=&quot;defaultLocal&quot; enabled=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;
    		&lt;catalog type=&quot;system&quot; id=&quot;https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/archetype-catalog.xml&quot; enabled=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;
    	&lt;/archetypeCatalogs&gt;

**Other causes**

Some people may also have upgraded to the latest 2022-12 edition of eclipse having remote catalogs in the `archetypesInfo.xml` file. They may also face the same issue changing it to the xml file also resolves this.

